The skull outline is triangular and elongated, with a slender snout that bears a slightly laterally expand- ed premaxilla in its anterior portion (
Fig. 5
). This skull morphology is also observed in the stereospondylomorph 

Platyoposaurus
(
Gubin, 1991
)

and in some advanced stereospondyls, such as 

Aphaneramma
(
Woodward, 1904
)

, and is usually related to a piscivorous habit (e.g. 
Gubin, 1991
, 
1997
; 
Dias & Schultz, 2003
; 
Eltink & Langer, 2014a
). It is also found in Crocodyliformes such as dyrosaurids, pholidosaurs, and thalattosuchians (
Brochu, 2001
).
